msgid "The denoising loop (DiT/UNet forward passes), shared across all models"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/support_new_models.md:0
msgid "`DecodingStage`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/support_new_models.md:0
msgid "VAE decoding from latent space to pixel space, shared across all models"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/support_new_models.md:34
msgid ""
"**Why recommended?** Modern diffusion models often have highly heterogeneous "
"pre-processing requirements — different text encoders, different latent "
"formats, different conditioning mechanisms. The Hybrid approach keeps pre-"
"processing isolated per model, avoids fragile shared stages with excessive "
"conditional logic, and lets developers port Diffusers reference code quickly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/support_new_models.md:36
msgid "Style B: Modular Composition Style"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/support_new_models.md:38
msgid ""
"Uses the framework's fine-grained standard stages (`TextEncodingStage`, "
"`LatentPreparationStage`, `TimestepPreparationStage`, etc.) to build the "
"pipeline by composition. Convenience methods like "
"`add_standard_t2i_stages()` and `add_standard_ti2i_stages()` make this very "
"concise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/support_new_models.md:40
msgid "This style is appropriate when:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/support_new_models.md:41
msgid ""
"**The new model's pre-processing can largely reuse existing stages** — e.g., "
"a model that uses standard CLIP/T5 text encoding + standard latent "
"preparation with minimal customization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/support_new_models.md:42
msgid ""
"**A model-specific optimization needs to be extracted as a standalone "
"stage** — e.g., a specialized encoding or conditioning step that benefits "
"from being a separate stage for profiling, parallelism control, or reuse "
"across multiple pipeline variants."
msgstr ""

